  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\">You are able to use your craft to great effect, to practice and explore your techniques while you earn your keep. You gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.xWY5omyIcILNR7y1]{Magical Crafting} feat, even if you do not meet its requirements. You can @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.QyzlsLrqM0EEwd7j]{Earn Income} with your visionary skill, even if it is a skill that normally does not have that capability. You can also @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.rmwa3OyhTZ2i2AHl]{Craft} magical scrolls, using your visionary skill in place of Crafting, but it must be of a spell you have in your portfolio that you can cast.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Special</span></span><span lang=\"EN\"> If your visionary skill is Crafting, you gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.QLeMH5mQgh28sa5o]{Specialty Crafting} feat, selecting Artistry as your specialty.</span></p>"
    },
